      "Acknowledge the opposing viewpoint before countering it — this strengthens your argument",
      "Use a range of persuasive techniques: rhetorical questions, direct address, evidence, humour",
      "Write in a register appropriate for a school magazine — semi-formal, engaging, confident",
      "Proofread carefully — SPaG marks are worth 16 of the 40 available",
